<title>USA: Sherwin-Williams raises qtly dividend.</title>
<headline>Sherwin-Williams raises qtly dividend.</headline>
<dateline>CLEVELAND 1997-01-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Sherwin-Williams Co said on Wednesday its board increased its quarterly common stock dividend from $0.175 per share to $0.20 per share on common stock, payable March 17 to shareholders of record on March 3.</p>
<p>The directors also declared a two-for-one common stock split to be distributed on or about March 28 to holders of record on March 3, 1997. The Company has about 85.9 million common shares outstanding.</p>
<p>The pre-split quarterly dividend of $0.20, payable on March 17 is the equivalent of $0.10 per share on a post-split basis, the company said. Sherwin said its last two-for-one common stock split was announced on February 20, 1991.</p>
<p>((New York newsdesk 212-859-1610))</p>
